procedures.name: Venipuncture

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.label: Blood Draw
procedures.description: Collection of venous blood for laboratory tests, including clinical chemistry, hematology, serology, HbA1c, pregnancy test, FSH, ethanol, pharmacokinetics (PK), pharmacodynamics (PD), and genetic sampling.

procedures.name: Urine Collection
procedures.label: Urine Sample
procedures.description: Collection of urine for urinalysis, pregnancy testing, and drug screening.

procedures.name: Insulin Infusion to Induce Hypoglycemia
procedures.label: Insulin Infusion
procedures.description: Intravenous (IV) insulin infusion to induce a state of controlled hypoglycemia, stopped once bedside plasma glucose is <60 mg/dL.

procedures.name: Nasal Glucagon Administration
procedures.label: Nasal Glucagon Admin
procedures.description: Administration of 3 mg LY900018 (nasal glucagon) for the treatment of insulin-induced hypoglycemia.

procedures.name: Intramuscular Glucagon Injection

code.decode: Therapeutic, prophylactic, or diagnostic injection; subcutaneous or intramuscular

procedures.label: IM Glucagon Injection
procedures.description: Administration of 1 mg intramuscular glucagon (IMG) for the treatment of insulin-induced hypoglycemia.

procedures.name: Vital Signs Measurement
procedures.label: Vital Signs
procedures.description: Measurement of supine blood pressure, pulse rate, and body temperature at specified time points.

procedures.name: Electrocardiogram

code.decode: Electrocardiogram, routine ECG with at least 12 leads; with interpretation and report

procedures.label: ECG
procedures.description: Recording of single and triplicate 12-lead ECGs at specified time points to monitor cardiac activity.

procedures.name: Bedside Plasma Glucose Monitoring
procedures.label: Bedside PG Monitoring
procedures.description: Frequent monitoring of plasma glucose levels at the bedside for safety during the hypoglycemia induction procedure and post-treatment.

procedures.name: Physical Examination
procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: Assessment of patient's physical health, including measurement of height and weight.

procedures.name: Nasal Inspection
procedures.label: Nasal Inspection
procedures.description: Visual inspection of the nasal passages performed pre-hypoglycemia induction and at 90 minutes post-treatment for all patients.

procedures.name: Injection-Site Assessment
procedures.label: Injection-Site Assessment
procedures.description: Assessment of the injection site for patients receiving intramuscular glucagon (IMG).

procedures.name: Edinburgh Hypoglycemia Scale
procedures.label: Hypoglycemia Questionnaire
procedures.description: Administration of a questionnaire to evaluate the recovery from clinical symptoms of hypoglycemia.

procedures.name: Intravenous Glucose Supplementation
procedures.label: IV Glucose
procedures.description: Administration of intravenous (IV) glucose if the patient experiences signs and symptoms of severe hypoglycemia requiring intervention.

medicalDevices.name: Nasal Dosing Device
medicalDevices.label: Nasal Glucagon Device
medicalDevices.description: A user-friendly, single-use, nasal dosing device that delivers 3 mg glucagon powder (LY900018) for absorption through the nasal mucosa.

medicalDevices.name: Syringe and Needle
medicalDevices.label: Syringe/Needle
medicalDevices.description: Device used for the intramuscular (IM) injection of reconstituted glucagon powder.

medicalDevices.name: Continuous Subcutaneous Insulin Infusion Pump
medicalDevices.label: CSII Pump
medicalDevices.description: An insulin pump used by some patients for their daily insulin therapy.

medicalDevices.name: IV Infusion Pump
medicalDevices.label: Infusion Pump
medicalDevices.description: Device used for the controlled intravenous infusion of insulin to induce hypoglycemia.

medicalDevices.name: Bedside Glucose Monitor
medicalDevices.label: Glucometer
medicalDevices.description: Device used for frequent monitoring of bedside plasma glucose (PG) levels for safety.

medicalDevices.name: 12-lead ECG Machine
medicalDevices.label: ECG Machine
medicalDevices.description: Diagnostic device used to perform single and triplicate 12-lead electrocardiograms.
